# ✅ **How to Launch an EC2 Instance (Amazon Linux 2 AMI) with User Data Script**

Below are the exact steps you will follow in the AWS Console.

---

# **STEP 1: Login to AWS Console**

Go to:

[https://console.aws.amazon.com](https://console.aws.amazon.com/)

---

# **STEP 2: Go to EC2 Dashboard**

Search **EC2** → click **Launch instance**.

---

# **STEP 3: Choose an AMI**

In **Application & OS Images**, select:

### **Amazon Linux 2 AMI (free tier eligible)**

— 64-bit (x86)

---

# **STEP 4: Choose Instance Type**

Select:

### **t2.micro** (Free Tier)

---

# **STEP 5: Configure Key Pair**

Choose an existing key pair or create a new one (to SSH later).

---

# **STEP 6: Configure Network (default is fine)**

- VPC: default
- Subnet: choose any
- Auto-assign public IP: **Enable**
- Security Group:
    - Allow **SSH (22)** from My IP

---

# **STEP 7: Add User Data Script**

Scroll down to **Advanced details** → **User data**.

Paste your script here (BASIC SAMPLE below).

---

## ✔ **Sample User Data Script (Amazon Linux 2)**

This script simply updates the instance and installs Apache (NO Python/Node files):

```
#!/bin/bash
yum update -y
yum install -y httpd
systemctl enable httpd
systemctl start httpd

echo "<h1>Welcome to Sunny's EC2 Instance With Linux AMI</h1>" > /var/www/html/index.html

```

This will:

✔ Update server

✔ Install Apache

✔ Start web server

✔ Add a simple HTML message

---

# **STEP 8: Launch Instance**

Click **Launch Instance**.

---

# **STEP 9: Test Your EC2**

After instance starts → copy **Public IPv4 address** → open in browser:

```
http://YOUR_PUBLIC_IP

```

You will see:

**Welcome to Sunny’s EC2 Instance!**
